packages <- c("tidyverse", "tidycensus", "tigris", "sp", "scales", 
              "ggspatial", "lubridate", "cowplot", "viridis", "grid")
invisible(lapply(packages, suppressPackageStartupMessages(require), character.only=TRUE, quietly=TRUE,
                 warn.conflicts = FALSE)) 
rm(packages)
setwd("/Users/taiebat/Desktop/Chicago-TNC-analysis/")
chicago_pickups <- read_rds("chicago_pickups.RData")
# Add some labels
d<-expand.grid(x=1:4,y=1:4)
d$text <- c("Low", rep("", times = 14), "High")


# compute quantiles (dividing into 4th) 
h.v<-quantile(chicago_pickups$cost_change_pct_mean,c(0.25,0.5,0.75,1), na.rm = T)
p.v<-quantile(chicago_pickups$estimate,c(0.25,0.5,0.75,1), na.rm = T)

chicago_pickups <- chicago_pickups %>% mutate(y= case_when(estimate<p.v[1] ~ 1,
                                                           estimate<p.v[2] ~ 2,
                                                           estimate<p.v[3] ~ 3,
                                                           TRUE ~ 4 ),
                                              
                                              x= case_when(cost_change_pct_mean<h.v[1] ~ 1,
                                                           cost_change_pct_mean<h.v[2] ~ 2,
                                                           cost_change_pct_mean<h.v[3] ~ 3,
                                                           TRUE ~ 4))

ggplot(data=chicago_pickups,aes(x=cost_change_pct_mean,
                                y=estimate,
                                color=atan(y/x),alpha=x+y))+
  geom_point(size=1)+  guides(alpha=F,color=F)+
  geom_hline(yintercept=p.v,color="gray20",linetype=2)+
  geom_vline(xintercept=h.v,color="gray20",linetype=2)+
  scale_color_viridis(name="Color scale")+theme_minimal()+
  theme(plot.caption=element_text(size = 9, hjust=0),
        panel.grid=element_blank())+
  scale_x_log10(breaks=c(h.v),
                labels=round(c(h.v),2)) +
  scale_y_log10(breaks=c(p.v),
                labels=round(c(p.v),2)) +
  labs( x = "Pecent Change in Cost of Trip After Policy",
        y = "Median Household Income")
## Warning: Removed 4 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

#### Make a legend
g.legend<-
  ggplot(d, aes(x,y,fill=atan(y/x),alpha=x+y, label=text))+
  geom_tile()+
  geom_text(alpha = 1, size=2)+
  scale_fill_viridis(option = "inferno")+
  #scale_fill_distiller(palette = "Reds")+
  theme_void()+
  theme(legend.position="none",
        axis.title=element_text(size=7),
        panel.background=element_blank(),
        plot.margin=margin(t=10,b=10,l=10))+
  theme(axis.title=element_text(color="black"))+ 
  labs(x="Median Household Income\nin 2018 inflation-adjusted $",
       y="Average Change\nin Trip Cost (%)")+
  theme(axis.title.y = element_text(angle = 90))


gmap<-
  chicago_pickups %>%
  filter(!is.na(cost_change_pct_mean_cut)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(fill=atan(y/x),alpha=x+y)) + 
  geom_sf(color = "grey", size = 0.05) + 
  theme_void()+
  scale_fill_viridis(option = "inferno")+
  #scale_fill_distiller(palette = "Reds")+
  guides(alpha=F,fill=F)+
  labs(title="Median Household Income and\nAverage Per-Trip Cost Change After Policy")

vp<-viewport(width=0.3,height=0.3,x=0.2,y=0.3)

print(gmap)
print(g.legend+labs(title=""),vp=vp)
